UK based provider of PayGo Solar home systems, Azuri Technologies and home entertainment satellite provider, Zuku last week hosted a cocktail party at the Muthaiga Gold Club, Nairobi, tolaunch the world&rsquo;s first complete pay-as-you-go satellite TV package. The new service targets households without electricity in the Kenyan market. In attendance were Director or Renewable Energy Isaac Kiva, Azuri CEO Simon Bransfield Garth and former Attorney General Charles Njonjo.